comments.text:
What's causing the difference is most likely baking tile spacing into an intermediate surface to allow repeating in the brush image shader.
The difference is so small that I am not sure whether it's worth undoing this for, but a solution could be to not do the baking and do decomposition in this case instead. I don't have a good sense of how often pages have repeated background images with spacing between repetitions (with lots of repetitions), but if it's rare it might be fine fine to abandon the baking.
comments.author: nical.bugzilla@gmail.com
